Thanks to Gilgurth for being extremely understanding.<br>
Thanks to Brendan for being a neutral evaluator.<br>
To the rest who ragged on me, please read my post in the bard section. It's a technical examination of some of the finer points of bard song twisting during raids.<br>
Raid leaders would benefit also.<br>
Not seeking contention, only understanding.<br>
&quot;Whoso keepeth his mouth and his tongue keepeth his soul from troubles&quot;<br>
<br>
Accent, Bard of the 48th song<br>
Trexate, Cleric of the 58 prayer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uazaule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azaule</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://web4.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/90/2197190.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/02 8:07:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=404.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://ldnews.kyid.net/images/members/azaule.jpg width=140 height=160></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reporting a &quot;been flamed&quot;, does that count?</span><hr size=1> Wow some people must have really pissed you off ... you posted all over the xroads...<br>
<br>
I have been in that situation as well but not on a vox raid. A lot of times you are doing the best job you can but it comes down to these people who are not pulling their own weight and hindering the progress. You know these people... the ones complaining about their pussy hurts and it's just too hard. WTF? Come on, some people have grown up in these nice and easy Kunark zones... and have no clue about how to function on a raid... not even that sometimes they don't know what the fuck to do because they never had this pressure on them to preform... and for what? To help kill a mob that they will possibly gain no loot from... so why bother to give more then 100%... let the other people there worry about that stuff...<br>
<br>
I realize a lot of what you have posted has come from  people sending to tells on how to do your job. You know a lot of these new bards have no clue of the flexibility and control we can have in a raid situation. They have conformed to a norm of what's to be expected of them and will not think outside the box for a little bit. Realizing that they can catch hell for trying something different or are not willing to do a lot more then what they were told to do. Be an example and let people know why you are doing a different twist... the reasons behind it. If they can't understand oh well... if they blame it on you when they all die because 1 bard tried to do something different... tried to compensate for what your party was lacking... then please tell them to STFU and be part of the solution not the problem.<br>
 <p>Azaule Singingfox<br>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=56427>My magelo profile</a><br>
